Installation Guide:
1. Download the .ijm file to your computer
2. Navigate to the plugins folder within your build of ImageJ/FIJI
	Mac: Right-click on the Icon and select view package contents
	Windows: Open the FIJI folder (usually in C:/
3. Create a new folder called “My Scripts” (or whatever you prefer)
4. Move the .ijm file into this folder
5. Re-start FIJI (or open it if it wasn’t running).
6. Check that the “My Scripts” (or equivalent) sub-category has been created under the “Plugins” Menu. (Hint: it will be in the lower items towards the bottom).
7. Check that the script has been installed.
